                	<div class="Painel"><p>
                    
                    DCL (Dependency Constraint Language) is a declarative, statically
checked, and domain-specific language that supports the definition of
structural constraints between modules. The main purpose of the
language is to support the definition of constraints between modules,
restricting the spectrum of dependencies that are allowed in
object-oriented systems.</p>

<p>One of the main advantages of DCL is its simple and self-explaining
syntax. The following figure summarizes the language syntax:<p>
